DRAGONWARE PRODUCTIONS (C) 1989

Space Shuttle launch sequence by Eric Zwirnmann

This Arc file should include:
			SHUTTL4S.SEQ   (requires min 1 MEG ST)
			READ_ME .DOC   (this file)

These files are of course free to pass around, all that is asked is that
they are always kept together.

For those of you saying, "Lets see that 'baby' launch!"  Well, here she is!

SHUTTL4S.SEQ  didn't take as long to make as the previous files SHUTTL1S and
SHUTTL2S.  I kind-of cheated when I made them.   To speed things up I just
saved two pictures 1) the shuttle and 2) the tower.  I then overlayed them
in cyber paint and animated the shuttle.  I then added the smoke (steam)
effect.  I found it to be quite impressive.  It came out much better than I
had hoped.  The original file (full screen and a few more frames) took
about 1.6Meg of memory and 1.1Meg as a saved file (SEQ).

Please send any comments or compaintes to:

			E.ZWIRNMANN  (GEnie)

